Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "grupi" in different forms and positions, with a star (*) marking the word:

1. *Grupi* se okupljaju u parku. (Groups are gathering in the park.)
2. Kako ćeš podeliti studente u *grupe* za projekat? (How will you divide the students into groups for the project?)
3. *Grupi* koja pobedi će biti dodeljena nagrada. (The group that wins will be awarded a prize.)
4. *Grupe* koje su stajale u redu su sada ušle u muzej. (The groups that were standing in line have now entered the museum.)
5. Potrebno je da se *grupišemo* kako bismo bili efikasniji. (We need to group up in order to be more efficient.)
6. *Grupisanje* u manje jedinice je neophodno u ovoj situaciji. (Grouping into smaller units is necessary in this situation.)
7. Kako bi se olakšalo *grupisanje* ljudi, postavljene su oznake sa brojevima. (To facilitate grouping of people, signs with numbers have been placed.)
8. Ovo je *grupno* zaduženje, tako da svi moraju učestvovati. (This is a group task, so everyone has to participate.)
9. *Grupna* dinamika je bitna za uspešan rad tima. (Group dynamics are important for successful team work.)
10. Za ovu vežbu je potrebno da *grupišete* reči prema njihovom značenju. (For this exercise, you need to group words according to their meaning.)